PROJECT 1: CHATBOT WITH RULE-BASED RESPONSES
Title
Rule-Based Chatbot Using C Language

Objective
To develop a simple chatbot that responds to user queries using predefined rules and conditional statements.

Description
A Rule-Based Chatbot is a simple AI application that interacts with users using predefined rules. The chatbot analyzes user input and generates appropriate responses based on keywords. This project demonstrates the basics of Artificial Intelligence and Natural Language Processing.

Algorithm
Start the program.
Accept user input.
Check whether the input contains predefined keywords.
Display the corresponding response.
Continue the conversation until the user enters "bye".
Terminate the program.
  
Source Code
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>

int main()
{
    char input[100];

    printf("===== RULE BASED CHATBOT =====\n");

    while(1)
    {
        printf("\nYou : ");
        fgets(input,sizeof(input),stdin);

        if(strstr(input,"hello") || strstr(input,"hi"))
        {
            printf("Bot : Hello! How can I help you?\n");
        }
        else if(strstr(input,"name"))
        {
            printf("Bot : My name is CodSoft Chatbot.\n");
        }
        else if(strstr(input,"how are you"))
        {
            printf("Bot : I am fine. Thank you!\n");
        }
        else if(strstr(input,"bye"))
        {
            printf("Bot : Goodbye! Have a nice day.\n");
            break;
        }
        else
        {
            printf("Bot : Sorry, I don't understand.\n");
        }
    }

    return 0;
}
